<title>USA: Grand Union sees restructure savings.</title>
<headline>Grand Union sees restructure savings.</headline>
<dateline>WAYNE, N.J. 1997-05-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Grand Union Co said Thursday it has initiated a corporate restructuring including lay-offs and division consolidations designed to save the struggling company more than $5 million.</p>
<p>The company said it will cut about 80 jobs at its Wayne, N.J., corporate headquarters. The announcement coincided with the company reporting huge year-end and fourth quarter losses.</p>
<p>&quot;We sincerely regret the necessity of laying off such a large number of valued Grand Union associates,&quot; board chairman and interim chief executive officer Roger Stangeland said in a press release.</p>
